content:
C# (C-Sharp) is a modern, object-oriented language developed by Microsoft â€” widely used for desktop apps, web apps (ASP.NET), and game dev (Unity). Here's your quick start guide to C# fundamentals.

---

## 1. Hello World
```csharp
using System;

class Program {
  static void Main() {
    Console.WriteLine("Hello, C# World!");
  }
}
```
Run it using Visual Studio or an online C# compiler.

---

## 2. Variables and Data Types
```csharp
int age = 25;
string name = "Dawar";
bool isCoder = true;
```

---

## 3. Conditionals and Loops
```csharp
if (age > 18) {
  Console.WriteLine("Adult");
} else {
  Console.WriteLine("Minor");
}

for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
  Console.WriteLine("Loop: " + i);
}
```

---

## 4. Methods (Functions)
```csharp
static string Greet(string user) {
  return "Hello, " + user;
}

Console.WriteLine(Greet("Dawar"));
```

---

## 5. Arrays and Lists
```csharp
string[] fruits = { "apple", "banana", "mango" };
foreach (string fruit in fruits) {
  Console.WriteLine(fruit);
}
```

---

## 6. Classes and Objects
```csharp
class Car {
  public string Brand;

  public void Honk() {
    Console.WriteLine("Beep!");
  }
}

Car myCar = new Car();
myCar.Brand = "Tesla";
myCar.Honk();
```

---

## 7. Properties and Constructors
```csharp
class Person {
  public string Name { get; set; }

  public Person(string name) {
    Name = name;
  }
}

Person p = new Person("Dawar");
Console.WriteLine(p.Name);
```

---

## 8. Exception Handling
```csharp
try {
  int x = 5 / 0;
} catch (DivideByZeroException e) {
  Console.WriteLine("Cannot divide by zero!");
}
```

---

## 9. Namespaces & Using
```csharp
using System.Text;

namespace MyApp {
  class Tools {}
}
```
Namespaces organize code, and `using` imports functionality.

---

## 10. Where to Use C#?
- Web apps with ASP.NET Core
- Windows apps with WinForms or WPF
- Game dev with Unity
- APIs, services, and more

---

## Final Thoughts
C# is powerful, clean, and beginner-friendly â€” great for modern enterprise and game development. Start small, explore LINQ, async programming, and dive into ASP.NET or Unity next.

